README for ADXL35 sensor test app
Author/Contact: Antonio Linan <alinan@zolertia.com>

Description:

This application simple polls periodically the ADXL345 sensor for data
and toggles a led when a specific axis is read:

 * X axis: red led.
 * Y axis: green led.
 * Z axis: blue led.

The data is printed over the serial port, using a client like putty or
picocom you can see the readings of the sensor adjusting the serial port
to this configuration:

bauds: 115200
bits: 8
parity: none

The ADXL345 sensor is a temperature sensor and its already integrated as
part of the Zolertia Z1 mote.

Tools:

None

Known bugs/limitations:

None.
